<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>and a few more....</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Plug-TP">Plug-TP</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:59 p.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> and a few more....<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=778" TARGET=_self>Changes needed for PvP to work in Everquest</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I agree with a lot of what Black says here that there definitely needs to be some modified code from what the PvE uses as to what PvP actually should do. A few levels apart as now means close to instant death for the lower level player due to resist and chance to hit.

<P>I do have a few other suggestions...
<P>1) Most people who play on the PvP server are not going to be looking to kill monsters and take many many hours to arrive at a decent character to play with in PvP situations. I would like to see monsters give many more times the amount of experience than they currently give. A level should take 30 minutes to an hour max to obtain at any point. Although I am not 100% on what increase of exp mobs should give on the PvP server...the current system is way too slow.
<P>2) Experience points lost on pvp combat. I dont know if this has been covered yet but I will throw it in. This is a pvp server..I am a large proponent of zero loss. Why? Few reasons. One, I wish to be engaged in pvp combat..not running around trying to kill mobs because I died and lost a level. Two, of course you lose connect and die. The whole point of a PvP server is to be fighting players...not killing mobs.
<P>3) Death and penalties. I like the idea of one item taken from the corpse. I would say that the person who does the most damage to the person gets to loot an item from the corpse..IE if 5 people attack the one who did the most damage out of the 5 to the person gets to loot an item. He also has 5 minutes to do this. After 5 minutes all items on the corpse are returned to the owner. Dont know if this is feasible but needs to be looked at in some form or another.
<P>4) Transportation. Again this is a PvP server dedicated to player combat. UO used moongates to travel across britania. Something similar should be used on the Equest PvP server. Dying and having to travel an hour to get back to your friends is not what I consider fun.
<P>Hope some of these suggestions help out.
<P>Plug
<BR>Guildmaster of The Pluggers
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
